<div ana="#b1" corresp="#elus0040.translation" subtype="transcription" type="edition" xml:id="elus0040.transcription" xml:lang="grc">
<p>
<g type="cross">+</g> Ἀνεπά<unclear>ε</unclear> ὁ μακά<unclear>ρ</unclear>
<lb/>ιος Γεώργιος
                    Βίκτω<lb/>ρ έν <expan>
<abbr>μη</abbr>
<ex>νὶ</ex>
</expan> Ξανθικῷ ιςʹ <expan>
<abbr>ἰ<lb break="no"/>νδ</abbr>
<ex>ικτιῶνος</ex>
</expan> ιβʹ ἔτους υογʹ<g type="cross">+</g>
</p>
</div>
<div ana="#b1" corresp="#elus0040.transcription" type="translation" xml:id="elus0040.translation">
<p>The Blessed George, son of Victor, went to his rest on the 16th of Xanthicos,
                    12th indiction, year 473.</p>
</div>
</body>
<back>
<div type="commentary">
<p>16 Xanthicos 473 Arabian Era = 6 April 578 CE. The 12th indiction actually began on 1
               September 578 CE: similar errors in noting dates are not uncommon on epigraphs.</p>
</div>
